Recommendation:
We recommended to the management to:
Create a team to conduct an immediate physical count of all its property, plant and equipment. This committee may be composed of the heads or representatives from the Office of the Municipal Treasurer, the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Engineer, and a representative from the Office of the Municipal Mayor. They are required to submit the RCPPE on or before January 31 of each year, copy furnished the COA Auditor concerned pursuant to Section 124 of NGAS Manual, Volume I;
Require each Department Head to conduct every year a physical inventory count of all properties under their office and to submit inventory report to the inventory committee for the random validation of the existence of the property; the reports should be reconciled with the accounting records to determine the correctness of the property records;
Require both the Accountant and Treasurer to prepare and maintain records and ledgers all properties owned by the Municipality;
The assigned committee should be required to check the condition of the property. Any damage, obsolete and unserviceable property shall be reported in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report and immediately request for disposal;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to trace and specifically determine the items under Property, Plant, and Equipment account through retrieval of supporting schedules in coordination with other concerned offices to ascertain the balances of the account as reflected in the year-end Financial Statement;
The Municipal Accountant should trace the period or date of acquisition of the assets and compute the depreciation based on the estimated useful life of assets as provided under COA Circular 2003-007. Prior years’ depreciation should be taken up as Prior Years Adjustment to be closed to Government Equity and adjust the same for the unaccounted accumulated depreciation for the year 2019

